<subSubSection id="C33D2F95D13DD607A8522DAD3521F895" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B987C1ED13DD607A8522DAD3521F895" blockId="28.[264,1323,427,1854]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B953A00CD13DD607A8522DAD37CFF945" bold="true" box="[312,426,1748,1774]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species, the third known, can be distinguished from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C27079DD13DD607ADD82DAD3703F8BD" authority="Koehler" authorityName="Koehler" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiomidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="alatum">
<emphasis id="B953A00CD13DD607ADD82DAD334EF946" box="[1202,1323,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O. alatum</emphasis>
Koehler
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27079DD13DD607A8C82D8534FEF8BD" authority="Koehler" authorityName="Koehler" box="[418,667,1788,1814]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiomidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="reductum">
<emphasis id="B953A00CD13DD607A8C82D853451F8BE" box="[418,564,1788,1813]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O. reductum</emphasis>
Koehler
</taxonomicName>
in having small granules at the margin and ventrally, a four­sided oral shield and in having 
<number id="3DEF6E39D13DD607ABDA2C5D34DAF895" box="[688,703,1828,1854]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="3.0">3</number>
armspines.
</paragraph>
